# Vokra Rust public-API snapshot — v1.0-rc window (M3-16-T03; rotated by M4-12).
#
# Regenerate with: scripts/rust-public-api-list.sh --update-snapshot
# Diff against with: scripts/rust-public-api-list.sh
# Audit only: scripts/rust-public-api-list.sh --audit
#
# Scope: pub API surface (candidate C, grep-based) of the three
# ABI-relevant crates: vokra-core, vokra-ops, vokra-capi.
# One line per public declaration, sorted, format:
#   FN     <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   STRUCT <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   ENUM   <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   TRAIT  <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   TYPE   <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   CONST  <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   STATIC <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   UNION  <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#   USE    <crate>::<module>::<path>|<normalized-line>
#   MOD    <crate>::<module>::<name>|<normalized-line>
#
# Honest limitations of the grep-based extractor:
#   * impl-block methods appear as bare FN <name>|<signature>.
#     Two impls sharing name AND signature collapse under sort -u.
#   * pub(crate) / pub(super) / pub(in path) are filtered out.
#   * Macro-generated pub items are invisible (source-level grep).
# The tree does not exercise any of these gaps; the freeze
# gate at M5-13 will re-evaluate the extraction strategy.
#
# See docs/abi-changelog.md for the semver policy and
# docs/tickets/m3/M3-16-abi-changelog.md for the WP scope.
